te support to clients when necessary. This will require travel and some weekend work.</li></ul><ul><li>Identify, and work to resolve, issues in the ticketing system by reporting to the appropriate department.</li></ul><ul><li>Report and provide input on feature requests and ticketing system enhancements that are requested by clients.&nbsp;</li></ul><ul><li>Participate in quality assurance and testing of new features and functionality, enhancements and bug fixes.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><em><strong>Experience working in the live event or&nbsp;event production industry&nbsp;is required.&nbsp;</strong></em></li></ul><ul><li>Experience working in Account Management and/or for a software company is preferred.</li></ul><ul><li>Strong written and verbal communication skills are essential to enhance client relationships and foster communication among ShowClix team members.</li></ul><ul><li>Excellent organization, time management, and prioritization skills.</li></ul><ul><li>Critical thinking and problem-solving skills needed to meet new account setup requirements and quickly handle client issues.</li></ul><ul><li>Ability to manage multiple tasks and projects with attention to detail and follow up.</li></ul><ul><li>Open, flowing communication is important. Must be friendly and genuinely interested in the business, agenda, and needs of others.</li></ul><p><strong>About ShowClix:</strong></p><p>Back in 2007, founders Lynsie Campbell and Joshua Dziabiak created ShowClix as an online ticketing and live event search engine. From a one-room office with a couple of computers and a ping-pong table, the company eventually evolved into the full-service event ticketing system that it is today.</p><p>Millions of tickets, three offices, and two cereal walls later, we&rsquo;re the preferred ticketing solution for thousands of performing arts theatres, live music venues, and festivals &mdash; as well as museums, non-profit fundraisers, nightclubs, even circuses and rodeos.</p><br />]]></description>
