			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Stop fetchin&#39; coffee and start an internship with an awesome team that works everyday with literally all sorts of events. We&#39;re seeking an enthusiastic <strong>Account Services Intern</strong> to work closely with our growing Account Management Department.</p>
<p>
	As an intern, this future event expert will back up our team as we build relationships with our primary ticket sellers. You&#39;ll also learn your way around a complete event ticketing system, along with a crash course in the ticketing operations of a variety of events. This includes everything from huge music festivals to touring circuses&mdash;and sometimes events that are just genuinely weird.</p>
<p>
	Everyone in our department (and really, our whole company!) is a multitasking pro who needs to learn how the platform works. Professional and patient communication skills are required, and you will be working alongside a diligent team who simultaneously manages the details for dozens of events every day.</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Learn your way around the ShowClix event ticketing system.</li>
	<li>
		Become an expert on management systems like Salesforce and Desk.com.</li>
	<li>
		Support members of the Sales and Account Management teams with various daily tasks.</li>
	<li>
		Team up with others to make sure our clients&#39; needs are met as quickly as possible.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		<strong><em>Experience working with events? Booked shows in the past? That&#39;s definitely going to get our attention, so mention it!</em></strong></li>
	<li>
		Savvy with software, spreadsheets and technology in general.</li>
	<li>
		Organized, efficient and able to juggle more than a handful of responsibilities.</li>
	<li>
		Confident and thoughtful communication skills.</li>
	<li>
		Critical thinking and problem-solving skills needed to meet new account setup requirements and quickly handle client issues.</li>
	<li>
		&quot;People skills&quot; i.e. &quot;I like working with / talking to / helping / being friendly with people!&quot;</li>
</ul>
<br />
<p>
	<strong>About ShowClix:</strong></p>
<p>
	ShowClix is proudly based in downtown Pittsburgh, PA, within walking distance of dozens of great restaurants and PNC Park. Internship perks include a competitive stipend, educational credit hours* and a truly rad office equipped with a snack wall and projection screen cinema lounge. To learn more about daily life at ShowClix, visit <a href="http://www.showclix.com/culture">http://www.showclix.com/culture</a>.</p>
<p>
	Back in 2007, founders Lynsie Campbell and Joshua Dziabiak created ShowClix as an online ticketing and live event search engine. From a one-room office with a couple of computers and a ping-pong table, the company eventually evolved into the full-service event ticketing system that it is today.</p>
<p>
	Millions of tickets, three offices, and two cereal walls later, we&rsquo;re the preferred ticketing solution for thousands of performing arts theatres, live music venues, and festivals&mdash;as well as museums, non-profit fundraisers, nightclubs, even circuses and rodeos.</p>
<p>
	<em>*Some universities apply.</em></p>
