<p>
	As Regional Account Executive, you will have the primary responsibility of establishing ShowClix and developing relationships with all ticket sellers in your market (likely within 100 mile radius of nearest major metro). You&rsquo;ll be tasked with owning your market by identifying, targeting and securing new clients and business opportunities. The majority of your time will be spent selling the ShowClix event ticketing system, and our related services and products.&nbsp; The right candidate will have a sincere appreciation and curiosity for people and their business, as well as knowledge and skills in how to successfully influence and persuade.</p>
<br />
<p>
	<strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<p>
	&bull; Develop a database of qualified prospects. Identify, target and secure new clients and business opportunities in your market.<br />
	&bull; Initiate action plans to approach (outbound) and secure new business in your market.<br />
	&bull; Establish and manage relationships with strategic partners and key players in your market by attending and networking at events, conferences and seminars. Some travel required.<br />
	&bull; Build and demonstrate expert product knowledge to allow for effective presentation of ShowClix&rsquo; ticketing software and services.<br />
	&bull; Maintain an accurate record of all sales and prospecting activities including sales calls, demonstrations, proposals sent and follow-up activities.<br />
	&bull; Manage and perform to a sales quota.<br />
	&bull; You will be selling to: Event organizers, Nightclubs, Live Music Venues, Performing Arts Theaters, Museums, Promoters, Sporting Teams/Facilities, Resorts, Conference Planners, Expos/Exhibitions, Tourist Attractions, Fairs, Festivals, &amp; Non-profits.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<p>
	&bull; 3+ years of B2B outside sales experience with a track record of consistently achieving aggressive sales targets is required.<br />
	&bull; Experience working for a software company and/or in the ticketing industry.<br />
	&bull; <strong>MUST be self-motivated</strong>, outgoing and well organized while managing several prospects at the same time.<br />
	&bull; Eager to sell! Ability to sell to and negotiate with prospects at all decision-making levels.<br />
	&bull; Should possess sound business judgment, recognizing the balance between achieving sales targets and maintaining or increasing pricing.<br />
	&bull; Ability to travel frequently.</p>
