<li>
Develop a database of qualified prospects. Identify, target, and secure new clients and business opportunities in your market.</li>
<li>
Initiate outbound action plans to approach and secure new business in your market.</li>
<li>
Establish and manage relationships with strategic partners and key players in your market by attending and networking at events, conferences and seminars. Some travel required.</li>
<li>
Build and demonstrate expert product knowledge to provide an&nbsp;effective presentation of ShowClix&rsquo;s&nbsp;ticketing software and services.</li>
<li>
Maintain an accurate record of all sales and prospecting activities including sales calls, demonstrations, sent proposals&nbsp;and follow-up activities.</li>
<li>
Manage and perform to a sales quota.</li>
<li>
You will be selling to the following markets: <em>Event Organizers, Nightclubs, Live Music Venues,&nbsp;Performing Arts Theaters, Museums, Promoters, Sporting Teams / Facilities, Resorts, Conference Planners, Expos / Exhibitions, Tourist Attractions, Fairs, Festivals,&nbsp;Non-profits.</em><br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
3+ years of B2B outside sales experience is required, along&nbsp;with a track record of consistently achieving aggressive sales targets.</li>
<li>
Experience working for a software company and/or in the event ticketing industry.</li>
<li>
<strong>MUST be self-motivated</strong>, outgoing and well-organized while managing several prospects at the same time.</li>
<li>
Eager to sell! Ability to sell to and negotiate with prospects at all decision-making levels.</li>
<li>
Should possess sound business judgment, recognizing the balance between achieving sales targets and maintaining or increasing pricing.</li>
<li>
Ability to travel frequently.</li>
</ul>
